data.name: ToolTipItem1.Text
data.value: Währungskurse / Exchange Rates This file includes the Euro foreign exchange reference rates and additional information for each currency being used. The additional information is an optional information and can be entered in the BAIS Application. Interface parameter for the method used must be set. Data from this file is transferred into target file WHGSTF.

data.name: ToolTipItem3.Text
data.value: KSA Ratingkürzel Kreditn.-Customer Rating Shortcut This interface contains the mapping table between the rating shortcut used by rating agencies and the borrowers customer number. The information is used in the standardized approach (KSA). Data from this table is transferred into target table KRKURF.

data.name: ToolTipItem4.Text
data.value: LCR/NSFR Zusatzinform. Kunden - add.inf. customers In this interface file additional customer information that is required for LCR and NSFR reporting can be submitted. Data from this file is transferred into target file KNEHMF. Only records with relevant information for customers should be provided. The fields MDANT and KDNRH must match with the values in table KNEIFF for the customer.

data.name: ToolTipItem5.Text
data.value: Sicherheiten Kredite/Loans assigned to collaterals In this file the loans are delivered against which the corresponding collateral should be calculated. Regarding securities for which former weightings (valid BEFORE Dec. 31, 2010) are to be used: Two loan records must be delivered fo the security with ISIN-A for SolvV and ISIN-A-ALT for GroMiKV. Data from this table is transferred into target table GAGEVF.

data.name: ToolTipItem6.Text
data.value: Sicherheiten Kopf / Collaterals master data This file contains the information for collaterals. Make sure to have discussed the possibilities and handling of collaterals with BSM. Data from this table is transferred into target table GAKOVF.

data.name: ToolTipItem7.Text
data.value: Kreditzusagen - Commitments This file contains commitments (given and received). For Leverage Ratio Reporting commitments that are fully drawn and where the repayment of the loan is open must be submitted too. The amount of undrawn commitments should be passed. As an option the amount of undrawn commitment can be calculated in BAISjava. To use this option careful analysis whether the algorithm impemented in BAISjava meets your requirements is crucial. Data from this table is transferred into target table ZUSAGF and in addition into target table ZUZKGF if necessary.

data.name: ToolTipItem9.Text
data.value: This interface will be used to built the balance history for AMM reporting to identify the parent contracts of a current contract, when the primary key has changed due to rollover, merge or assignment. Relations 1:n between old and new contracts are possible.

data.name: ToolTipItem10.Text
data.value:
In dieser Schnittstelle können Wertberichtigungen für Geschäfte und Kreditzusagen angeliefert werden. Die Geschäfte müssen in der Geschäftsdatei GSTBIF vorhanden sein, d.h. es muss sich um bilanzielle Geschäfte oder traditionell außerbilanzielle Geschäfte handeln. Die Kreditzusagen müssen in der Datei ZUSAGF vorhanden sein. Für Kreditzusagen werden nur Daten für die aktuelle EWB, Länderwertberichtigung und EWBs für die SolvV berücksichtigt.
Alle Beträge sind ohne Vorzeichen anzuliefern.
In der LiqV werden die endfälligen Kredite und die Kreditzusagen um die EWB-, PWB- und EWB für Länderrisiko gekürzt. Bei Tilgungs- und Annuitätendarlehen werden EWB, PWB und EWB für Länderrisiko anteilig auf die jeweiligen Laufzeitbänder verteilt. Ist der Schnittstellenparameter BKOIFF auf J gesetzt, werden die angelieferten Abschreibungs- und Einzelwertberichtigungsbeträge für die Meldung der Bewertungskorrekturen in der BISTA berücksichtigt. Die Schnittstelle BKOIFF muss dann nicht mehr beliefert werden.
Ist der Schnittstellenparameter GSWBIF/EWB auf J gesetzt, dann werden die Einzelwertberichtigungen bei der BISTA, Grundsatz I und LiqV berücksichtigt. Eine zusätzliche Kompensation ist dann nicht erforderlich. Für Kreditzusagen erfolgt die Berücksichtigung der EWBs unabhängig von diesem Parameter.
Der Schnittstellenparameter SOLVVEWB/AKTUELL steuert, ob in der SolvV und in der Groß- und Millionenkreditmeldung (im Zusammenhang mit dem Parameter GROMIKV_SPEZK_EWB) die aktuellen EWBs und PWBs berücksichtigt werden sollen (EWBBT; PWBBT) und dadurch in den Felder EWBBS und PWBBS geschrieben werden (SOLVVEWB/AKTUELL=J) oder ob die in der Schnittstelle anngelieferten Beträge EWBBS und PWBBS berücksichtigt werden gemeldet werden. (SOLVVEWB/AKTUELL=N z.B. nach der Feststellung des Jahresabschlusses).
Beim Befüllen der festgestellten EWB per GSWBIF ist zu beachten, dass die festgestellten EWB möglicherweise nicht zum aktuellen Saldo des Geschäfts passen. Außerdem kann der Fall auftreten, dass Konten, für die eine festgestellte EWB existierte, zum Meldestichtag bereits abgewickelt sind.

data.name: ToolTipItem11.Text
data.value: LCR/NSFR Zusatzinformationen Geschäfte/Zusagen/WP In this interface file additional information related to accounts/transations, commitments and security master data that is required for LCR and NSFR reporting can be submitted. Data from this file is transferred into target file GSTBIF, ZUSAGF and WPSTAF respectively. The target file is specified by the value in field MODUL. If MODUL = ZU target table is ZUSAGF (loan commitments) and the values of field MDANT, KDNRH and GSREF must be equal to fields MDANT, KDNRH and ZUREF in interface file ZUSIFF. If MODUL = WP target table is WPSTAF (security master data) and the values of field MDANT and GSREF must be equal to fields MDANT and WPKNR in interface file WISEMF. In all other cases target table is GSTIFF (account/transaction master data) and the values of field MDANT, MODUL, KDNRH, KTONR and GSREF must be equal to field MDANT, MODUL, KDNRH, KTONR and GSREF in interface file GSTIFF.

data.name: ToolTipItem12.Text
data.value: KSA Kunden-/Länder-Rating-customer/country ratings This interface contains the customer and country ratings. The information is used in the standardized approach (KSA). Data from this table is transferred into target table KSRATF.

data.name: ToolTipItem13.Text
data.value: Gruppen verbund. Kunden - Groups of conn. clients This file delivers borrower units. Borrower units always represent a couple consisting of unit and borrower information; this allows a multilayer construction. Data from this table is transferred into target table KNVKNF.

data.name: ToolTipItem15.Text
data.value: Cashflow derivatives and securities. In case of lending business, cashflow must be delivered until residual debt is 0, i.e. if the residual debt at the end of an interest period is not 0, cashflow must be calculated with the same conditions until residual debt is 0. For deposit business, cashflow must be delivered until end of interest period. If cash-inflow, all amounts must be negative. If cash-outflow, all amounts must be positive. Cashflows for commitments given must be positive and cashflows for commitments received must be negative. If data in interface file KGCIFF and KGLIFF (time buckets) is submitted, the setting of variable parameter LIGS/KGCIFF determines how time buckets for LiqV and balance sheet of residual maturities are calculated. Value=N: information in KGCIFF is ignored. If information for a transaction is available in KGCIFF and KGLIFF the information in KGCIFF is ignored if parameter value is set to value I, otherwise information from KGCIFF is used. Data from this file is transferred into target table KGCFLF

data.name: ToolTipItem17.Text
data.value: Salden Konten/Geschäfte - Account balances This file contains balances of accounts or transactions. The account or transaction is specified by MODUL, KDNRH, KTONR and GSREF and an entry must exist in interface file GSTIFF or master file GSTBIF in a corresponding manner. Data from this table is transferred into target table GSTFIF.

data.name: ToolTipItem18.Text
data.value: Konten/Geschäfte - Account/transaction master data This file includes all customer and internal accounts and all balance sheet transactions. A specific account or transaction is specified by the values in columns MODUL,KDNRH,KTONR and GSREF. Data from this file is transferred into target file GSTBIF
